		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64267528"><p>Authentication is built on encryption. It can be symmetric (with a shared secret learned at pairing) or asymmetric (with sharing of public keys at pairing). But neither does a thing to protect against relay attacks.</p><p>Part of the vehicle side of the security is built on the assumption that the fob is range-limited (push-to-start is a proximity system requiring the fob to be "in range" as well as answer an authenticated challenge response), and relay attacks break that assumption. It's the same as if I take you<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64267528">

</div>
