	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64267546"><p>How would public/private keys prevent the man in the middle attack going on here?</p><p>Those prevent someone from pretending to be a host and sending a *different* message from the intended one; or from reading the contents of the message.  Here, we&#226;(TM)re talking about pretending to be a host and send *the same* message.  Usually we don&#226;(TM)t care if someone does that, because all we care about is the contents of the message.  Here though, what we care about is the fact that the message was sent at all<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64267546">

