	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64267100"><p>After all that you suggested something that is not a solution. They laid out clearly they are already employing a strategy that can work equivalent to your solution, but the problem is the authenticator is always on and always ready and willing to answer any challenge.</p><p>The fundamental problem is that they verbatim retransmit packets between the car and the authorized key fob.  The emulator problem is due to picking a stupidly small key space, for some reason.  The emulator portion can and in some cars is bei<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
