<ul id="commtree_64267372"><li id="tree_64267854" class="comment oneline"><span class="ind"></span>
<div id="comment_status_64267854" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64267854" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64267854" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64267854" name="comment_link_64267854" href="//it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23237496&amp;cid=64267854" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64267854)" >Re:</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64267854" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64267854); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>2</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~Junta">Junta</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~Junta">( 36770 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64267854"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64267854"><p>Though even that would be limited. For example, I am walking around inside and it's in my pocket. The accelerometer *still* drives it to stay on. It would mitigate, by handling the "it's in a drawer" or "it's on my purse on the counter" scenarios, but folks don't always do that.</p><p>An answer would be expiring the challenge within 15ns, in which case relay attacks can't overcome the speed of light.  This might have to be 15ns over a very tight deterministic fixed interval, but ultimately there would need to be n<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64267854">

</div>
</div>

